<paragraph id="8B958E04FF99740224DCFD7B8B2CFD0A" blockId="4.[151,1436,677,1063]" box="[198,801,717,743]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
Description of male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF9974022631FD7B8A9BFD0A" box="[555,662,717,743]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Figs 4–8</figureCitation>
: 
<typeStatus id="549130A6FF99740226BBFD7B8B19FD0A" box="[673,788,717,743]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Holotype</typeStatus>
):
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B958E04FF99740224DCFD438B37FBCA" blockId="4.[151,1436,677,1063]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
Genital capsule rotated clockwise through approx. 90° (degree and direction probably not significant – see 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AF587FF997402248DFCAB894DFCDB" authorityName="Ricardo" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,320,797,822]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Perasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transvaalensis">
<emphasis id="B95E5216FF997402248DFCAB894DFCDB" box="[151,320,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">transvaalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Epandrium in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF99740226B2FCAB8AFCFCDA" box="[680,753,797,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than wide (length: breadth ration = 1: 1.07), in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF9974022580FCF389ECFCB2" box="[410,481,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) broad, with broadly rounded proximal and distal ends and slightly curved. Proctiger in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF9974022597FCDB89D9FC6A" box="[397,468,877,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) clearly distally bilobed and projecting well beyond epandrial lobes. Hypandrium in ventral view tapering slightly to broadly curved distal end (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF9974022761FC238BC9FC42" box="[891,964,917,943]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF9974022133FC238D99FC42" box="[1321,1428,917,943]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Figs 4–7</figureCitation>
) with somewhat rectangular appearance, dorsal lobe robust (hidden from view in dry condition); gonostylus in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF997402252BFC53897AFC12" box="[305,375,997,1023]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with rounded apex bearing a slightly backwardly-directed dorsal spine. Aedeagal base in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="13119281FF9974022522FBBB8973FBCA" box="[312,382,1037,1063]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) lacking distally directed projections.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF55DE8CFF997402248DF8198B79F804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" targetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" targetPageId="4">
